The Original Raging Bulls are still among America's favorite hunting handguns. Chambering the popular and powerful .44 Magnum and 454 Casull rounds, the mighty 444 and 454 revolvers are built for a lifetime of tough use. Referred to as factory tuned porting and gas expansion chamber for recoil and makes shooting comfort a reality.
 	Taurus Security System (TSS)rs
Taurus family of semi-auto pistols all feature the Taurus Security System, which provides instant-ready defense with built-in ability to secure your pistol and make it inoperable at the turn of a key. When the Security System is engaged, the pistol cannot be fired or cocked and the gun's manual safety cannot be disengaged. As with our revolver Security System, the device is part of the firearm and cannot be lost, and the same special Security Key works for both the revolver and pistol Systems (two keys come with each gun). To engage: simply insert the Key into the button on the rear or side of the pistol and rotate one-quarter turn clockwise. This engages the Security System. The manual safety cannot be moved and the trigger cannot be pulled. To disengage: simply rotate the key one-quarter turn back. This releases the Security System, yet leaves the pistol's manual safety in the "safe" position until you are ready to release it yourself and fire the gun.
 	Transfer Bar
The transfer bar mechanism prevents the hammer from striking the firing pin unless the trigger is pulled fully to the rear.

title: For Sale:  Aimpoint ML3 2 MOA w/ Larue LT152 Mount
postcontent:
For sale is a lightly used Aimpoint ML3 sitting in an LT152 mount.  This model does not have night vision settings, and features the (generally preferred) 2 MOA dot versus the standard 4 MOA dot.  Please note this mount sits lower (1.2" optical centerline from top of rail) than standard Aimpoint mounts, and if you have a standard AR-15 front sight this mount will not work.  It is intended for non-AR firearms, or AR's with a folding front sight.  The only parts that show any use are slight wear marks on the underside of the mount where it attaches to the firearm (completely hidden when mounted, and in no way alters fit/function).  Comes with a set of flip-caps, box, manual,  batteries, and Aimpoint synthetic body cover.  If bought new from Larue Tactical this combination would cost the better part of 200 dollars more expensive than asking price...save yourself some dough and take mine off my hands!  Not looking for trades, but you never know if the right one came my way!

Generic info on Aimpoint ML3:  

Unique features for CompML3
Designed for day use, including dusk and dawn
New ACET technology allows 50,000 hours of operation on one battery
Available in 2 dot sizes (2 and 4 MOA)
Submersible to 135 feet (45 meters)
Comes with replaceable outer black rubber cover

Generic info on Larue LT152 mount:

Designed for the RASII, but equally at-home wherever a short mount is desired.
This QD mount for the Aimpoint Comp M2 is 1/2" shorter than the standard Comp M2 mount to fit a RAS II. It has a 30mm ring and hard-locks to any Picatinny rail.

The LT152 positions the centerline of the optic 1.20" above the top of the rail.

Like all LaRue mounts, it is precision-machined out of bar-stock aluminum and matt black anodized to provide a durable non-reflective surface finish. The locking LaRue Speed Lever provides outstanding return to zero; the optic can be removed, and replaced, without loss of zero. Guaranteed.

It's a Century Arms imported AK74 that has been converted using a Izmash-based Bull-pup kit. The fore-arm (forward portion) of the kit is not original and was custom built for this particular firearm by the previous owner. I have had no problems with it holding zero with my EOTECH. The gun fires and works flawlessly. As a reminder (might be informative for some) that this particular bullpup kit utilizes metal linkage for the trigger/firing mechanism so it's a bit sloppy which is TYPICAL. If you're expecting this rifle to be a .25 MOA 1,000 yard rifle then this isn't for you. This is in fact an amazing run-n-gun firearm that I've used in a few different games. It's compact allowing you to utilize in positions that you would struggle with other guns. Accuracy wise, it's a 1.25-1.5 MOA rifle at 100 yards. Most of my experience with this rifle has come from well under 100 yards, where it shines brightest. I did at one point have the intention to bring it back to it former glory (with buttstock!) but opted to keep the bullpup as it fit perfectly.

Comes with MAGPUL BUIS and 1,000 rounds of 5.45x39

I am not interested in any trades whatsoever.
